OL,4,Cfor child sex abuse disclosures
OL,6,FShe said that many children described
OL,7,Fnot being believed or made to feel
OL,8,Fguilty for not being grateful for the
OL,9,Fattention they had received from the
OL,10,Fperpetrator.
OL,12,FMs Farris added that it was important
OL,13,Ffor the new legislation to strike a
OL,14,Fbalance between prioritising the
OL,15,Fsafety of the child, whilst also
OL,16,Fensuring that it did not risk over-
OL,17,Fpenalising people who care for
OL,18,Fchildren in informal and voluntary
OL,19,Fsettings.
